fs.fibu2.view.model
Class BilancialInformation

java.lang.Object
  fs.fibu2.view.model.BilancialInformation

public final class BilancialInformation
extends java.lang.Object

A BilancialInformation is an immutable tupel of bilancial sums for a fsfibu2 journal table row. It contains sums for:
- The sum of all entries (up to a certain point)
- The sum of all entries in certain categories
- The sum of all entries in certain accounts PLUS the starting values
All elements can be publicly modified

Author:
Simon Hampe

Method Detail

increment

public BilancialInformation increment(Entry e)
Returns:
The bilancial information obtained by adding the value of e to the overall sum, its category and account mapping (If there is no mapping, it is created). If e == null, a clone of this information is returned.

decrement

public BilancialInformation decrement(Entry e)
Returns:
The bilancial information obtained by incrementing with an entry which is identical to e, except that is has value ( - e.getValue())
